Items.Title: Newton’s Third Law Activity || Low-Cost Experiment with Plastic Box & Refill Waste ||
Items.Description:
In this video, we demonstrate Newton’s Third Law of Motion – “For every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction” – using a simple, low or almost zero-cost activity.
With just a plastic box and waste refills, you can easily perform this fun and effective experiment at home or in the classroom.
This activity is part of #activity_based_learning to make science simple, engaging, and practical.
Perfect for students, teachers, and science lovers, this experiment shows how powerful Newton’s laws are in our daily life.

✨ What you will learn in this video:

Concept of Newton’s Third Law

How action and reaction forces work

Low-cost science experiment idea for schools

Fun DIY demonstration for Physics

👉 Watch till the end and try this activity yourself. Don’t forget to like, share, and subscribe for more such easy and engaging science experiments.
